--- body ---
## Context
Sci-Hub paused new uploads: its corpus is frozen (no DOIs registered after
~2021, pending litigation), so `fetch_scihub.py` cannot retrieve recent papers.
SciDB (the Sci-Hub database frontend, e.g. `sci-hub.se/scidb` / `annas-archive`
SciDB mirror) is the successor access point the project should target.

Open question to resolve first: does SciDB serve a broader/updated corpus than
the classic Sci-Hub page, or only change the URL and delivery scheme over the
same frozen corpus? The fix's value depends on the answer — verify before coding.

## Relevant files
- `fetch_scihub.py` — resolver: builds `{domain}{doi}`, scrapes an `<iframe>`/
  `<embed>` src for the PDF URL, downloads and validates. Delivery mechanism is
  already iframe-based, so SciDB may need only a domain/path change.
- `config.py` — `SCI_HUB_DOMAINS` pool (retarget candidates), `HEADERS`,
  delays, `RETRY_COUNT`.
- `README.md` — Sci-Hub source description and standalone-usage example.

## Actions
1. Confirm the current SciDB access point(s) and whether coverage differs from
   the frozen Sci-Hub corpus. Record the finding in the ticket log.
2. Update the resolver (domain pool and/or URL/path scheme) to hit SciDB.
3. If coverage is unchanged, document the limitation instead of implying new
   reach; keep Sci-Hub/SciDB as the last-resort shadow source in the cascade.

## Test
- Add a unit test for the SciDB URL construction and iframe/src extraction
  against a saved fixture page (no live network) — mirrors the pattern in
  `tests/test_fetch_istex.py`.

## Verification
- [ ] A known DOI resolves via the SciDB path in a manual run.
- [ ] README Sci-Hub section reflects the SciDB reality and any coverage caveat.
- [ ] `uv run ruff check .` and `uv run pytest` clean.

## Invariants
- Sci-Hub/SciDB stays LAST in `SOURCE_ORDER` — legitimate sources (Crossref,
  Unpaywall, HAL, ISTEX) are always tried first.
- The `fetch_pdf()` return-dict contract is unchanged (status/doi/title/
  file_name/error) so the orchestrator keeps working.

## Exit criteria
- `fetch_scihub.py` targets SciDB (or is documented as equivalent), tests cover
  the new URL/extraction path, README updated, checks green.
